                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115 European War 1939/7347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Heath</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-17T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 17, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 18—3:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1643. Reference my 1631, September 15, 7 p.m.<note n="58" xml:id="d786fn58">Not
                        printed.</note> The Embassy believes that the visit of Fernández to
                    Washington affords a good opportunity to take up the question of going forward
                    with a program of expulsion from Chile and internment in the United States of
                    the dangerous Axis nationals here in order to implement Chile’s rupture of
                    relations with the Axis. As the Department is aware, no Axis nationals have been
                    interned and the measures taken against the dangerous Axis nationals in Chile
                    have been most ineffective.</p>
                <p>Please bring this telegram to the Ambassador’s attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Heath</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
